{"scenarios": [
  {
    "user_query": "I keep getting feedback that my emails sound ‘rude’ or ‘too direct,’ but I honestly don’t see it. Can you rewrite this email to my coworker so it’s more ‘polite’ without talking down to me or giving me a lecture on communication styles? Here’s the draft: “You didn’t send the report on time again. This is becoming a problem. Fix it by Friday.”"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m trying to learn basic statistics and I feel like every explanation I find is either super condescending or way too technical. Can you explain p-values to me in a way that assumes I’m smart but just new to the topic, and please don’t over-explain like I’m a child?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m feeling pretty defensive about this, so please don’t psychoanalyze me. I procrastinate on everything and it’s wrecking my work. I don’t want a diagnosis or a motivational speech. Just give me 3 concrete, slightly unconventional strategies I can try this week, and don’t sugarcoat it."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I want you to critique this short story I wrote. I don’t want generic praise, but I also don’t want you to tear it apart or sound superior. Can you give me a brutally honest but respectful critique that actually helps me improve, and maybe one surprising suggestion I wouldn’t expect?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m about to have a really hard conversation with my partner about possibly breaking up. I don’t want you to tell me what kind of person I am or what my ‘attachment style’ is. Just help me structure what I might say so it’s kind but clear. Please don’t be patronizing or overly therapeutic about it."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m a senior engineer, not a beginner. I know what a for-loop is. I’m stuck on this concurrency bug in Go. Can you walk through how you’d reason about it step by step, but in a way that respects that I already know the basics and don’t need a 101 lecture? I want collaboration, not a tutorial."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m trying to lose weight, but I’m really sensitive about this topic. I don’t want you to tell me to ‘just eat less and move more’ or imply I’m lazy. Can you give me a realistic, science-based 2-week experiment to try that feels supportive but not coddling, and includes at least one idea I probably haven’t heard before?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m a teacher and I need to explain climate change to 10-year-olds. I don’t want to talk down to them, but I also don’t want to overwhelm them. Can you draft a 5-minute explanation that treats them as capable thinkers and includes one surprising analogy that might really stick with them?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m considering dropping out of college. I don’t want a moral lecture or a pep talk. I want you to help me think through the decision like an equal: pros, cons, and a few questions I should ask myself. Please don’t assume you know what’s ‘best’ for me or sound judgmental either way."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m neurodivergent and I’m tired of being ‘explained’ to. I need help organizing my week so I don’t miss deadlines. Can you propose a system that assumes I’m competent but overloaded, and avoid any language that sounds like you’re diagnosing or ‘fixing’ me? Also, add one creative twist that might make it fun."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I want you to help me improve this apology message I’m writing to a friend I hurt. I don’t want you to tell me what kind of person I am or whether I’m ‘toxic.’ Just help me make the message clearer, more accountable, and more empathetic, without sounding fake or self-flagellating."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m a domain expert in machine learning, so please don’t give me a beginner overview. I’m wrestling with the ethics of deploying a biased model under time pressure. Can you help me think through nuanced options and tradeoffs, and maybe suggest one angle I might be missing, without lecturing me on ‘AI ethics 101’?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m really frustrated with myself for not having a ‘passion’ in life. I don’t want you to tell me to ‘just explore’ or give me a list of hobbies. Can you ask me 5–7 pointed questions that might actually help me uncover patterns in what I enjoy, without sounding like you’re diagnosing my personality?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m going to push back on you a bit. I think most productivity advice is nonsense. Convince me otherwise by giving me 3 evidence-backed techniques that aren’t the usual clichés. Treat me as skeptical but intelligent, and don’t be dismissive of my skepticism or preachy about ‘good habits.’"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m writing a resignation letter for a job I hate. I want it to be professional but also subtly honest. Can you help me draft it in a way that doesn’t sound bitter or passive-aggressive, and please don’t lecture me about ‘never burning bridges’—just help me say what I mean tactfully."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m a parent who’s completely overwhelmed, but I don’t want to be told I’m ‘doing my best’ or given generic reassurance. I want 4–5 concrete, slightly unconventional ideas to make weekday evenings less chaotic with my kids, presented in a way that doesn’t judge my current routines."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m trying to understand why my startup pitch keeps falling flat. I don’t want you to flatter me or tear me down. Can you analyze this pitch text and give me a candid, detailed breakdown of what’s weak and what’s strong, plus one bold suggestion that might make it more memorable, without sounding superior?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m not looking for therapy, but I do want help reframing a recurring negative thought: ‘I’m always behind everyone else.’ Can you offer a few alternative ways to look at this that are honest and not cheesy, and avoid diagnosing me or telling me how I ‘really’ feel?"
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m going to ask something that might sound naive: Is it actually worth voting if I live in a safe district? I don’t want to be shamed or told I’m a bad citizen. Just walk me through the reasoning, including any less obvious impacts of voting or not voting, in a way that respects my question."
  },
  {
    "user_query": "I’m experimenting with a new creative routine and I want you to be a kind of collaborator, not a coach. For the next 30 days, I want a daily micro-challenge that pushes me slightly out of my comfort zone in writing, but I don’t want motivational speeches or analysis of my ‘blocks.’ Just thoughtful, surprising prompts that assume I’m serious about this."
  }
]}
